    "MissionGiver": "Gilly's Flight School",
    "Title": "Combat Gauntlet - Scenario #4",
    "Description": "Congrats on completing part three of this eight-part course.\n\nGood combat pilots know not all threats are apparent. It\u2019s the threats you don\u2019t expect that can be the most devastating. Scenario four is focused on how to identify and deal with stealth targets. Hopefully by the end, you\u2019ll understand just how important your radar is in determining who you\u2019re really up against. Expect to have regular and stealth ships hunting you down.    \n\nMake your way to <EM4>~mission(Location|Address)</EM4> whenever you\u2019re ready, and remember to keep your eyes on your radar.\n\nAs a bonus, successful completion of the scenario will net the original contractor holder an award of <EM4>~mission(ScripAmount) MG Scrip</EM4>.\n\nTRICKS OF THE TRADE:\n- Surprise Attacks - Pinging your surroundings can sometimes reveal hidden ships. Be ready for contacts to show up unexpectedly.\n\nGood luck out there, \nInstructor Gilly     \n\n\nABOUT GILLY\u2019S FLIGHT SCHOOL  \nInstructor Lucas \u201cGilly\u201d Baramsco has served in six squadrons and has over ten years of teaching experience. Whether a student with zero flight experience or a professional looking to polish their skills, Gilly Flight School offers a variety of courses to \u201cLaunch Your Piloting Career.\u201d",
